{
  "stem": "4284.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When we had gotten there, we could not exactly see what was going on, but there was a peculiar odor, but, you know, the building was tall.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The facilities were such that you couldn't see what was going on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When we got out to the place trying to dry ourselves with the clothing we just had, here were camp police, or kapos, as they were, which were inmates.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And with batons, they beat you-- rush, rush, hurry.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Move over there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Do this.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Do that.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they said, welcome to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "That was the first time that we knew where we had arrived.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "After all this procedure and processing, that's the first time that we knew.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Well, it wasn't actually Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Auschwitz was really the total name for the railroad facility that existed long before World War II which happened to be, just by coincidence, the geographical confluence of many, many European countries' railroad facilities.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And that's why the Germans chose this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "From every country they occupied-- including Germany, Poland, whatever-- railroads would go there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Nobody understood why.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It was a sleepy little town of nothing, just a railroad facility.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Well, now I was in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Birkenau, I was in the camp C, which is-- they just had A, B, and C.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They did have something.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They called it Zigeunerlager, which was for non-Jews, political prisoners, or gypsy, which is what Zigeuner means.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We had no idea what would happen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We had no idea what we were there for because we had never heard about Auschwitz or Birkenau or anything in all these years.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "To us, it was just another camp, maybe another ghetto, except when you looked around and you see barracks after barracks after barracks and people languishing there and just laying around, sitting there.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
